"""Pydantic v2 models autogenerated from ../../../../schemas/*.schema.json.

DO NOT EDIT THIS DIRECTORY BY HAND. To regenerate, run from the monorepo root:

    just codegen-dagster

This module is generated from the JSON Schemas in `schemas/`, which are
themselves generated from the Rust output structs in
`engine/crates/rocky-cli/src/output.rs` (and `commands/doctor.rs`) via
`schemars`. The full chain is:

    Rust struct (#[derive(JsonSchema)])
        --(rocky export-schemas)-->
    schemas/<command>.schema.json
        --(datamodel-code-generator)-->
    types_generated/<command>_schema.py

Note: this __init__.py is restored by the `just codegen-dagster` recipe
after each run, since datamodel-code-generator overwrites it with an
empty stub.

The generated classes use the Rust type names. The hand-written classes
in `../types.py` use Python-flavored names. The two sets coexist today;
follow-up work will swap structured-command consumers to the generated
types and add backward-compat aliases.

Covered commands (Phase 2 rounds 1-8 — ALL CLI commands now typed):

  Structured: discover, run, plan, drift, state, doctor
  Compile/test/CI: compile, test, ci
  Operational: optimize, history (+ model_history), metrics
  AI: ai, ai_sync, ai_explain, ai_test
  Lineage: lineage (+ column_lineage)

Known oddity: ``rocky_core::checks::CheckDetails`` is a Rust untagged enum
with five variants. schemars emits ``oneOf``; datamodel-code-generator
materializes it as ``CheckResult1`` through ``CheckResult5`` inside
``run_schema``, and ``TableCheckOutput.checks`` is typed as the union of
those five. Functional but ugly variant names; deferred.

Shared types (Diagnostic, Severity, SourceSpan, TestFailure, DriftSummary,
DriftActionOutput) appear in multiple generated modules because the
top-level command structs that reference them are independent. The
top-level package re-exports each shared type from one canonical module.
"""

